title: Beside the Ocean ~
description:
Hi there! welcome to "Beside the Ocean" (Drawing Process) - Click/Tap on the character to continue :D
========================================

Instruction: Click on the character

This is a pretty simple drawing process, I never draw a detailed looking boy before so let's just call this as a practice xD (let me know what do you think in the comment section below) ^^

This was drawn using scratch 2.0 vector editor, in this project I'm showing how I draw a basic head shape, face, shadings, hair, and details

not perfect... I know... there's a lot more to learn, it's been a while since the last time I draw a detailed image. Not sure why, but the boy turned out preetty ;u; he reminds me of Yato from Noragami xD

the background is a blurred image of a beach
Music by MorningLightMusic from YouTube :D
========================================
thank you for watching ^u^
Leave a love/heart if you liked my drawing, and please be respective in the comment section below :D

title: ghost town

title: Out of This World
description:
Back from a hiatus! I hope you enjoy this drawing; it definitely took quite a while to complete this art but I am happy with the result. What killed my art block was actually a scholarship contest I entered for this piece. There is a hidden six letter word within the drawing, see if you can find it without context!

Onto other matters, I've been quite busy with academics and projects outside of Scratch. That explains my lack of activity (sorry for the profile comments I have yet to respond to!) But as a small tease, @Will_Wam and I are planning to host something special for Smash Ultimate, so definitely stay tuned for that! :)

title: Day in the Life: A Desk
description:
The animation loops forever until you tell it to stop.

Music: "G Piano" found on www.soundofpicture.com
Artwork: Created in Illustrator. The desk is *loosely* modeled after my own - my desk is definitely not this clean though lol 
Font: Adam.CG Pro
Sound effects: found on freesound.org

Be sure to check out the SDS "Day in the Life" Studio: https://scratch.mit.edu/studios/6234813/
instructions:
The new SDS theme is called "Day in the Life" and I'm super excited about it! It invites you to imagine what a day in the life of whatever you can imagine might be.

When I first thought about what I might want to make for the the studio, the idea of showing a day in the life of a desk quickly popped into my mind and I decided to run with it :P Here is a somewhat minimalist animation of what a day in the life of a desk might look like :)

Be sure to check out the SDS "Day in the Life" Studio. What will you create? https://scratch.mit.edu/studios/6234813/

instructions:
W I N D - A   P L A T F O R M E R | B Y   @SMILINGOUIDO
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
It's so windy... You can't move backward and your'e going to move faster... And faster... Can you reach your home?
Tip: Press A/Left arrow when a new level starts to stand still and R to reset an Level if you got stuck.
---
Use W/up arrow to jump(On mobile: Tap over the player).
Use D to speed up(On mobile: Tap behind the player).
Use A to slow down(On mobile: Tap before the player).
Use R to restart the level(On mobile: Tap on the Player).
Use M to mute/unmute the music.
Use the skip button to skip an Level.
All instructions are in game.
All levels are possible!
Have fun!

title: Portal
description:
---Click the Green Flag twice---

(doesn't support mobile devices)

-Instructions-
>WASD or Arrow Keys to move
>Point and click to create portals
> Don't touch the acid (purple)
>"q" for blue portal
>"e" for red portal
>"r" to reset the portals
>"p" to restart the level

-Notes-
> I made this program for the AP Computer Science Principles exam. If you have any questions about that class, you can ask me and you should really take it.
> Drop a Love. Fav, and Follow!!!
> This probably took me ~2 weeks to make
> Comment any bugs you see since the portals are kind of buggy.\
> Shooting a portal on yourself won't work (due to a lot of issues with collisions and stuff).

-Credits-
All art and program is made by me @Gligar35
Music is from the Sprite Library...still looking for a good theme music...
